MOSCOW , November 1 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- A Russian official said today that Russia and Japan should handle their bilateral affairs , especially sensitive issues , very cautiously .
To seek a hasty settlement on the sensitive issues could result in new problems , said Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Grigory Karasin in an interview with Inter -fax news agency .
Referring to the bilateral dispute on fishing and territory , Karasin said that both countries agreed that only through sound and positive relations in various fields can a solution to these complicated matters be found , <ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">The informal summit between Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto this weekend in the Siberian city of Krasnoyarsk will guide the development of the two countries ' constructive relations , said Karasin .</ENAMEX>
The minister said both Russia and Japan cordially hoped to cooperate in various fields .
The territorial dispute between the two countries has been a big obstacle to a peace treaty formally ending World War II hostilities .
Japan is demanding the return of four Pacific islands , known in Russia as the Southern Kuriles and Japan as the Northern Territories .
They were seized by Soviet troops in the final days of the war .
